topic.title: Provisioning and De-provisioning

section.title: Client Mapping Datapath Segment Provisioning
section.p: The g5_api_client_map_cfg() API provides the following mapping options for Ethernet Subsystem or Interlaken sourced traffic.

li.p: Transparent Ethernet traffic from the Ethernet Subsystem that is GMP/BMP OTN mapped.
Terminated Ethernet traffic from the Ethernet Subsystem that is GMP/BMP/GFP OTN mapped.
Ethernet traffic that is terminated at the Interlaken interface and is GMP/BMP/GFP OTN mapped.
Packet traffic that is terminated at the Interlaken interface and is GFP OTN mapped.
FlexE clients that are terminated and their packet payloads are GFP OTN mapped.
FlexE clients that are IMP OTN mapped transparently.

section.p: Figure 1 shows the transparent Ethernet traffic sourced from the ENET block(A) and sent through the ECPB to the MAPOTN subsystem to be GMP/BMP OTN mapped and then the resulting ODUk is sent to the OCPB block(B) of the COREOTN subsystem.

fig.title: Client Mapping Datapath Segment Provisioning: Transparent Ethernet Traffic OTN Mapped

section.p: Figure 2 shows the terminated Ethernet traffic sourced from the ENET block(A) and sent through the ECPB to the MAPOTN subsystem to be OTN mapped and then the resulting ODUk is sent to the OCPB block(B) of the COREOTN subsystem.

fig.title: Client Mapping Datapath Segment Provisioning: Terminated Ethernet Traffic OTN Mapped

section.p: Figure 3 shows the terminated Ethernet traffic from an Interlaken channel from the DCPB block(A) to the Ethernet Subsystem and then through the ECPB block and sent to the MAPOTN subsystem to be GMP/BMP/GFP OTN mapped and then the resulting ODUk is sent to the OCPB block(B) of the COREOTN subsystem.

fig.title: Client Mapping Datapath Segment Provisioning: Interlaken Sourced Ethernet Traffic OTN Mapped

section.p: Figure 4 shows the terminated packet traffic from an Interlaken channel from the DCPB block(A) to the MAPOTN subsystem to be GFP OTN mapped and then the resulting ODUk is sent to the OCPB block(B) of the COREOTN subsystem.

fig.title: Client Mapping Datapath Segment Provisioning: Packet Traffic OTN Mapped

section.p: Figure 5 shows the datapath configured from the FlexE block(A) through the Ethernet Subsystem to the ECPB(B) for FlexE clients that are terminated and their packet payloads are OTN mapped or the FlexE clients are OTN mapped transparently.

fig.title: FlexE Datapath Segment Provisioning: FlexE OTN Mapped Traffic

section.title: Client Mapping Datapath Segment Provisioning API Details
section.p: The g5_api_client_map_cfg() API provisions MAPOTN segment, CoreOTN FO2 as well as any other segments and mapping connections to ECPB and DCPB data paths based on the provided mode and channel ID. The API parameters are shown below with any associated enumerated types.

The device_id parameter is the device instance. For transparent Ethernet segment provisioning, the matching Ethernet channel from the g5_api_enet_prov() API is used for the chnl_id. For terminated Ethernet segment provisioning, the matching Ethernet channel from the g5_api_enet_prov() API is used for the chnl_id of g5_api_client_map_cfg() API.
The client mapping mode is specified by the parameter mode of the g5_api_client_map_cfg() API uses the g5_client_adaptation_mode_t enumeration.

section.p: The parameter client_num_incr of the g5_api_client_map_cfg() API specifies the number of 1.25G tributary slots required to transport the GFP client in ODUflex(GFP) or 25G bit rate increments required to transport the FlexE client in ODUflex.
The parameter gfp_slice of the g5_api_client_map_cfg() API specifies the explicit GFP slice assignment or automatic slice assignment. This is used for GFP modes only.

section.title: Client Mapping Datapath Segment De-provisioning API Details
section.p: The g5_api_deprov() API is used to de-provision client mapping datapath segments. The parameters and associated enumerated types are below.
The device_id parameter is the device instance. The chnl_id parameter of the API is the channel ID for the Ethernet client port or Interlaken channel ID to be de-provisioned.

The enumerated type g5_deprov_t of the g5_api_deprov() API defines the scope of resources that are cleaned up as part of a de-provisioning operation when a partial or completely configured datapath is torn down. The enumerator G5_DEPROV_SEGMENT_MAPPER de-provisions the mapper component of the Ethernet client port or Interlaken packet channel chnl_id only up to the OCPB. The enumerator G5_DEPROV_PATH_MAPPER de-provisions the chnl_id and any children of the chnl_id including de-provisioning of connected child IDs until the mapper functionality is completely removed. The primary chnl_id associated with these mapper functions will be retained. If there is no mapper in the datapath the behavior of G5_DEPROV_SEGMENT is followed when it is called for a Ethernet port or Interlaken packet chnl_id that includes mapper functionality. In this case the primary chnl_id is maintained and the mapper and anything connected to the mapper is removed.

section.title: Example Code
section.p: The following example code can be used to create a MAPOTN segment. Note that the mapping operation is 1:1 hard linked with the client side channel which could be Ethernet or Interlaken, as such, this operation takes in the same chnl_id as an earlier call to g5_api_enet_prov() or g5_api_ilkn_pkt_prov().
section.codeblock:
UINT32 device_id = 0x8817; UINT32 enet_odu_chnl_id = 0x3000;
rc = g5_api_client_map_cfg(device_id, enet_chnl_id, G5_MAP_ODU4_100GE_GMP, // mode 0, // client_num_incr G5_GFP_SLICE_CFG_AUTO); // gfp_slice
